To set a stack and establish it as the current stack, the program or operating system/executive must do the following 

1) Establish a stack segment 

2) Load the segment selector for the stack segment into the SS register using MOV, POP, or LSS instruction 

3) Load the stack pointer for the stack into the ESP register using a MOV, POP, or LSS instructions. The LSS instructing can be used to load the SS and ESP registers in one operation 
